 BY BAMIDELE FAMOOFO Leading dealers in the Nigerian equities market transacted business worth about N1.17trillion in the first half of 2022. The figure accounts for 70.16 percent of total trade value on the Nigerian Exchange Limited between January 4, 2022 and June 30, 2022. The top 10 Stockbroking firms were also responsible for 70.65 percent of the total volume of shares that exchanged hands on the NGX platform in the review. The firms, according to data supplied by the NGX at the end of June, exchanged about 108.14 billion shares for N1.17 trillion in the review period. Top among the leading firms was Cardinalstone Securities Limited which accounted for 30.63 percent or N510.76 billion of the total turnover value registered by the 10 leading Stockbroking companies. Cardinal Stone Securities Limited also took the lead in turnover volume, accounting for 47.17 percent of total trade volume. APT Securities and Funds-BRD emerged the second leading Stockbroking firm in value terms with about N154.08 billion, accounting for 9.24 percent of turnover value. It was third on the volume chart with 5.67 billion representing 3.7 percent of total volume done by the 10 firms. StanbicIBTC Stockbrokers Limited achieved about N107.3 billion, accounting for 6.44 percent of turnover value in six months while Meristem Stockbrokers Limited accounted for 5.3 percent of turnover value representing about N88.31 billion as EFG Hermes Nigeria Limited occupied fifth position on the value chart with about N74.28 billion representing 4.45 percent of total trade value by the 10. Other firms on the top 10 value table are Cordros Securities Limited, N70.0 billion or 4.2 percent; Chapel Hill Denham Securities Limited, N51.57 billion or 3.09 percent; CSL Stockbrokers Limited, N50.88 billion or 3.05 percent; Rencap Securities (Nig) Limited, N34.4 billion representing 2.06 percent and FBN Quest Securities Limited, accounting for 1.69Â  percent of turnover value at about N28.24 billion. 